{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:psalms.44",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 44,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 44 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.44.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:1",
      "text": "We have heard with our ears, God; our fathers have told us what work you did in their days, in the days of old.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.44.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:2",
      "text": "You drove out the nations with your hand, but you planted them. You afflicted the peoples, but you spread them abroad.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.44.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:3",
      "text": "For they didn’t get the land in possession by their own sword, neither did their own arm save them; but your right hand, your arm, and the light of your face, because you were favorable to them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.44.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:4",
      "text": "God, you are my King. Command victories for Jacob!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.44.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:5",
      "text": "Through you, we will push down our adversaries. Through your name, we will tread down those who rise up against us.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.44.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:6",
      "text": "For I will not trust in my bow, neither will my sword save me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.44.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:7",
      "text": "But you have saved us from our adversaries, and have shamed those who hate us.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.44.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:8",
      "text": "In God we have made our boast all day long. We will give thanks to your name forever. Selah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.44.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:9",
      "text": "But now you rejected us, and brought us to dishonor, and don’t go out with our armies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.44.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:10",
      "text": "You make us turn back from the adversary. Those who hate us take plunder for themselves.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.44.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:11",
      "text": "You have made us like sheep for food, and have scattered us among the nations.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.44.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:12",
      "text": "You sell your people for nothing, and have gained nothing from their sale.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.44.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:13",
      "text": "You make us a reproach to our neighbors, a scoffing and a derision to those who are around us.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.44.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:14",
      "text": "You make us a byword among the nations, a shaking of the head among the peoples.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.44.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:15",
      "text": "All day long my dishonor is before me, and shame covers my face,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.44.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:16",
      "text": "at the taunt of one who reproaches and verbally abuses, because of the enemy and the avenger.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.44.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:17",
      "text": "All this has come on us, yet we haven’t forgotten you. We haven’t been false to your covenant.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.44.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:18",
      "text": "Our heart has not turned back, neither have our steps strayed from your path,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.44.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:19",
      "text": "though you have crushed us in the haunt of jackals, and covered us with the shadow of death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.44.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:20",
      "text": "If we have forgotten the name of our God, or spread out our hands to a strange god,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.44.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:21",
      "text": "won’t God search this out? For he knows the secrets of the heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.44.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:22",
      "text": "Yes, for your sake we are killed all day long. We are regarded as sheep for the slaughter.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.44.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:23",
      "text": "Wake up! Why do you sleep, Lord? Arise! Don’t reject us forever.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.44.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:24",
      "text": "Why do you hide your face, and forget our affliction and our oppression?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.44.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:25",
      "text": "For our soul is bowed down to the dust. Our body clings to the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.44.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:26",
      "text": "Rise up to help us. Redeem us for your loving kindness’ sake.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
